Most every tech writer you run into will complain bitterly if they have to work in Word. 
However, we’ve all done it, and we’ll all have to do it again. 
Many small companies are willing to pay for an Office license for most everyone, and don’t want to jump for other tools. 
However much you argue with it, you will have to use Word in your career.
You will also have to make at least a few PowerPoint presentations. 
Surprisingly, Excel is also rather useful with tech writing.
